  "description": "Positive known-answer vectors for the off-chain rfc9162-sha256 leaves-list artefact. The leaves-list is the canonical-CBOR (RFC 8949 §4.2.1) file that carries the leaf digests committed by an on-chain merkle[] entry. Required map keys are format, tree_alg, root, leaves, leaf_count; leaf_alg is optional and informative. Canonical map-key order is bytewise-lexicographic on the encoded keys: root (4B) < format (6B) < leaves (6B) < leaf_alg (8B, when present) < tree_alg (8B) < leaf_count (10B). Each case pins the canonical encoding both without and with the optional leaf_alg key (sha2-256); decode(cbor) recomputes the root from the leaves per RFC 9162 §2.1.1 and matches it against the declared root, and encode(decode(cbor)) == cbor byte-for-byte. The root values match the rfc9162-sha256-root-kat vectors. Every cbor_hex MUST be produced byte-identically by conforming implementations.",
